Contents of x3c/ were provided by X3C.
The libraries are compiled under 64-bit gcc-4 linux.  Binaries for 
other architectures are not available.

Other code is (c) 2012 Walter Brisken, but is based heavily on
X3C example program: lf1ReaderSample.cpp

Building Instructions
---------------------

If you are checking out code from SVN you will need to run the next four
commands to generate the build file and configure insfrastructure:

aclocal
autoconf
autoheader
automake -a


To configure and build the code:

./configure   # other options, such as --prefix may be supplied here

make


To install:

make install

